title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link
type="local"
href="field-0001.xml"
addr="field-0001"
title="Field">Field</fr:link> (but it could be any commutative ring, however nice you want it). Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> be a formal variable. Consider the <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Ring of Formal Distributions</html:dfn> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}[{[x,x^{-1}]}]]]></fr:tex> which consists of generic formal power series like
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[f(x)=\sum ^{\infty }_{n=-\infty }a_{n}x^{n}.]]></fr:tex>
Consider the specific function
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\delta (x)=\sum _{n\in \mathbb {Z}}x^{n}]]></fr:tex>
Then
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[x\delta (x)=\delta (x)]]></fr:tex>
so
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[(1-x)\delta (x).]]></fr:tex>
But <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[1-x\neq 0]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\delta (x)\neq 0]]></fr:tex>, so <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}[{[x,x^{-1}]}]]]></fr:tex> has <fr:link
type="local"
href="ra-000E.xml"
addr="ra-000E"
title="Zero Divisor">zero divisors</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
